      },
      "lineNbr": 76,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-31T00:16:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "same as in NewClient before, this is not a good interface: nobody should specify in prod code allowInsecure\u003dfalse.\n\nSo, either:\n* make this method private, though I prefer to have it public s.t. code can validate configs before actually using them.\n* revert to original implementation which relied on mockUrl for tests, just like gitiles.\n\nI prefer the latter in order to keep code consistent with gitiles interface.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 76,
        "startChar": 42,
        "endLine": 76,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "f95353738531461581480d5bd8148ea68a217dae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fef9b99f_c7471de4",
        "filename": "common/api/gerrit/gerrit.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 76,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118104
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-31T20:17:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So I decided that what I liked best was to:\n\n- Provide an interface that a third party user can implement (.get in this case) for their own tests.\n- Make NewClient (now NewProdClient) always validate and assume secure host.\n- Make internal tests use the private attribute of the struct to set the url\n  and bypass validation.\n\nPTAL at the latest patch.",
      "parentUuid": "d1ffc6b2_9b32cb7e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 76,
        "startChar": 42,
        "endLine": 76,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "f95353738531461581480d5bd8148ea68a217dae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5f21d844_f5ddef5b",
        "filename": "common/api/gerrit/gerrit.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 76,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-01T17:30:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ll respond to the rest on newest patchset, but let me try to persuade you against\n\n\u003e Provide an interface that a third party user can implement (.get in this case) for their own tests.\n\nImagine I add later another method to Gerrit\u0027s Client which I need for say scheduler, but nobody else does. This new method will need to be added to this interface you\u0027ve created to east testing. Unfortunately, adding a new method to interface now requires every user of this interface to implement this new method even though they never use it.\n\nInstead, each third party user should define their own interface of things they actually depend on. Then, if library gains a new method, no third party user code needs to be updated.",
      "parentUuid": "fef9b99f_c7471de4",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 76,
        "startChar": 42,
        "endLine": 76,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "f95353738531461581480d5bd8148ea68a217dae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
