        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-31T00:16:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "so I actually also at first embedded host (url) into client, but changed my mind during review. I am not strongly in favor of either, but regardless of which one we choose, IMO we must be consistent between gitiles and gerrit clients.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 119,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 119,
        "endChar": 47
      },
      "revId": "f95353738531461581480d5bd8148ea68a217dae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "febdeb47_103ce4c8",
        "filename": "common/api/gerrit/gerrit.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 119,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118104
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-31T20:17:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t foresee a use case where the same client has to be used with multiple hosts, and as a user, having the url validated in the process of creating a client is rather convenient, also reduces the param list for the apis.\n\nI\u0027d vote for changing gitiles client to work this way.",
      "parentUuid": "8e504e20_dab0169b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 119,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 119,
        "endChar": 47
      },
      "revId": "f95353738531461581480d5bd8148ea68a217dae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
