    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6d4d9436_78f428e2",
        "filename": "common/api/gerrit/gerrit.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 137,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-31T00:16:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Unfortunately, this is misleading, even though technically true. `S` can be used for paging, but you probably don\u0027t want to. Instead, \"after\" and \"before\" (or \"age\") should be used for reliable paging.\n\ntl;dr possible races between sequential reads for different \"pages\" \u0026\u0026 writers\n -\u003e paging which will get some duplicate CLs \u0026\u0026 will completely miss others\n\nIf you actually need paging, lmk, we can discuss how to do it properly.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 137,
        "startChar": 44,
        "endLine": 137,
        "endChar": 63
      },
      "revId": "f95353738531461581480d5bd8148ea68a217dae",
